trg_text: State Visit to Tanzania and SADC SummitCabinet has received a report on President Cyril Ramaphosa s State Visit to the United Republic of Tanzania, which also included a business delegation to advance intra Africa trade and investmen As part of the outreach programme, the President also visited Morogoro, which hosted South African freedom fighter He laid a wreath at Mazimbu Tower in honour and memory of all South Africans who died in exilPresident Ramaphosa also led the South African delegation to the 39th Southern African Development Community (SADC) Ordinary Summit of Heads of State, where his Tanzanian counterpart, President John Pombe Magufuli, assumed the Chairpersonship of the SADIn his capacity as the SADC Facilitator to the Kingdom of Lesotho, President Ramaphosa presented a report on developments in the facilitation process during the SADC Troika Summit of the Organ on Politics, Defence and Security Cooperation held on Friday, 16 August 201 28th BASIC MeetingCabinet has acknowledged the 28th Brazil, South Africa, India and China (BASIC) Climate Change meeting that took place in Brazil from 14 to 16 August 2012 Cabinet also welcomed the ambitious climate change action undertaken by BASIC countries in support of international agreements in the pre- and post-2020 period, notwithstanding the multiple socio-economic challenges these countries are faced wit Cabinet supported the call by the BASIC countries for developed countries to provide adequate finance, technology transfer and capacity-building to facilitate the effective implementation of the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change, its Kyoto Protocol and the Paris Agreement in a manner that does not increase the indebtedness of developing countrie Cabinet decisions1.
